  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 13-15.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - These three verses (the counterparts of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 6:26, 28, 40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") are not in the parallel. Although we can scarcely trace the principle of their selection from the seven parts of the prayer, they would seem to have been selected from the original work, as samples of a reply which presumably embraced reference to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "all",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the seven. When, in ver. 14, it is said, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "I will heal their land",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the telling expression, according to the Authorized Version, must be understood to refer to the removing of drought by rain. On the other hand, the Authorized Version is, in ver. 15, unfortunate in the unnecessary and misleading insertion of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "italics",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " found there, and in the use of the preposition \"in\" for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "of",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the simple case ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "construct",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which is manifestly what is wanted and intended. It was not absolutely essential that prayer should be made in the place. How many references there are to prayer being made from a distance ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "toward",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the place! 2 Chronicles 7:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
